Additional and up-to-date information is available here:

[PBooks Installation][]

REQUIREMENTS
============

1.  PHP 5.2+
2.  MySQL 5
3.  PHP Extentions: mysqli, xslt
4.  PEAR Libraries: Cache_Lite, MDB2, MDB2#mysqli
5.  Nexista



INSTALLATION
============

Debian
------

1.  Install into /usr/share/pbooks/
2.  chown www-data /usr/share/pbooks/cache/
3.  cd /var/www/
4.  ln -s /usr/share/pbooks/web pbooks
5.  Install database (next section)
6.  Login to http://your-hostname-here/pbooks/auth.php?nid=login


XAMPP
-----

Visit [PBooks Installation on Ubuntu][] for instructions on how to do this.

DATABASE INSTALLATION
=====================

1.  Install db with phpmyadmin.
2.  The default username and password are demo / demo.
3.  Login.


DATABASE UPDATE
===============

This process is done manually, and will not be required under normal
circumstances.


CONFIGURATION
=============

1. cd /usr/share/pbooks
2. cp config/config.xml.dist config/config.xml
3. vim config/config.xml
4. vim apps/pbooks/config/config.xml


GENERAL NOTES
=============

* The [PBooks forums][] are checked regularly.
* The [PBooks mailing lists][] are low volume and actively monitored.


